'''Jean-Kévin Duverne''' (born 12 July 1997) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[KAA Gent|Gent]] on loan from French club [[FC Nantes|Nantes]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
Duverne made his [[RC Lens]] first team debut on 5 August 2016 against [[Tours FC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/08/05/france/ligue-2/racing-club-de-lens/tours-football-club/2237925/|title=Racing Club de Lens Vs Tours Football Club|date=5 August 2016|access-date=2 September 2023}}</ref>

On 2019 he joins [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]] and on 30 August 2023 Duverne joins [[FC Nantes]] as [[free agent]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=43442|title=JEAN-KÉVIN DUVERNE EST NANTAIS !|date=30 August 2023|access-date=2 September 2023|language=fr}}</ref>

On 29 January 2025, Duverne moved to [[K.V. Kortrijk|Kortrijk]] in Belgium on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=K.V. Kortrijk|url=https://www.kvk.be/nieuws/kvk-presenteert-volgende-aanwinst/|title=Jean-Kevin Duverne is volgende KVK-aanwinst|trans-title=Jean-Kevin Duverne is the next KVK acquisition|date=29 January 2025|access-date=29 January 2025|language=nl}}</ref> On 8 September 2025, he returned to Belgium on a new loan with [[KAA Gent|Gent]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=KAA Gent|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/nieuws/08-09-2025/duverne-komt-van-nantes-naar-gent|title=Duverne komt van Nantes naar Gent|trans-title=Duverne comes from Nantes to Ghent|date=8 September 2025|access-date=21 December 2025|language=nl}}</ref>

==International career==
Duverne was born in France and is of Haitian descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lenational.org/a-liste-selectionnes-deux-derniers-matches-grenadiers/|title=À quand la liste des sélectionnés pour les deux derniers matches des Grenadiers ?|date=24 August 2016|publisher=|access-date=18 May 2018|archive-date=18 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180518131049/http://www.lenational.org/a-liste-selectionnes-deux-derniers-matches-grenadiers/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 17 May 2018, he was called up to represent the [[France national under-20 football team]] at the [[2018 Toulon Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://festival-foot-espoirs.com/festival/detail_actualite.php?id=2961|title=La liste de la France pour le Festival Espoirs 2018|publisher=}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] for a set of [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in June 2024, and scored on his debut, a 2–1 win over [[Saint Lucia national football team|Saint Lucia]] on 6 June 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://haitiantimes.com/2024/06/07/haiti-beats-saint-lucia/|title=World Cup Qualifier: Unconvincing Haiti comes from behind to defeat Saint Lucia 2–1|first=Onz|last=Chéry|date=7 June 2024|website=The Haitian Times}}</ref>

